# MLSECDEVOPS GitLab Pipeline CI -- MarkLLM watermark-evaluation group (heavy).
# NOTE: this group is intentionally NOT hash-locked by lockfile-audit — its multi-GB
# closure exhausts the small runner when pip-compile downloads it to hash, and it is
# already vuln-audited at these exact pins by the dedicated markllm-deps-audit job. This
# file remains the single source of the markllm/torch/transformers pins for that audit.
# Pins mirror MARKLLM_VERSION / TORCH_VERSION / TRANSFORMERS_VERSION in
# .gitlab-ci.yml and are also audited by the markllm-deps-audit job. transformers
# stays on 4.x -- markllm 0.1.5 predates the 5.x major and pins huggingface_hub<1.0
# / Pillow==9.4.0, which is why this heavy stack is locked on its own rather than
# folded into the core group. See requirements-ci.in for the grouping rationale.
# torch is pinned to the CPU-only wheel: the default PyPI build pulls the ~2 GB CUDA
# stack (nvidia-* deps) onto CPU-only CI runners, which exhausted the small runner's
# disk ([Errno 28]) when `lockfile-audit` hash-compiled this group. The +cpu wheel
# (~200 MB, no nvidia deps) is served from the PyTorch CPU index below, and the +cpu
# local-version forces resolution there. Mirrors the markllm-watermark-eval install.
--extra-index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cpu
markllm==0.1.5
torch==2.12.0+cpu
transformers==4.57.6
